The paper proposes two efficient Bloom Multifilters for solving multiple set matching problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with membership queries and set matching, which are common problems in databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the optimization of space efficiency, which is a common concern in cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CR, and cs.AI, in that order.
